<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1323,398,945]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,416,398,424]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Description.</emphasis>
Female with character states of 
<emphasis box="[806,1024,399,424]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diamphidaxonella</emphasis>
(male unknown). Dorsal edge of camerostome acutely rounded anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[868,961,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="36.[264,382,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[300,1317,317,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[264,1323,310,1751]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Diamphidaxona (Diamphidaxonella) brevitarsa sp. nov., adult female. 69, dorsal shield; 70, ventral shield and genital field; 71, pedipalp; 72, gnathosoma, lateral view; 73, leg I; 74, distal segments of leg IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[927,961,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="70.0">70</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pedipalps with tibia bearing one ventral seta (
<figureCitation box="[462,549,479,505]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="36.[264,382,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[300,1317,317,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[264,1323,310,1751]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Diamphidaxona (Diamphidaxonella) brevitarsa sp. nov., adult female. 69, dorsal shield; 70, ventral shield and genital field; 71, pedipalp; 72, gnathosoma, lateral view; 73, leg I; 74, distal segments of leg IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[516,549,479,505]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="71.0">71</number>
</figureCitation>
). Dorsal shield with anterior plate of same width as posterior plate and weakly pointed anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[632,720,519,545]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="36.[264,382,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[300,1317,317,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[264,1323,310,1751]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Diamphidaxona (Diamphidaxonella) brevitarsa sp. nov., adult female. 69, dorsal shield; 70, ventral shield and genital field; 71, pedipalp; 72, gnathosoma, lateral view; 73, leg I; 74, distal segments of leg IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[687,720,519,545]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="69.0">69</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral shield with suture lines between third and fourth coxal plates with medial loops deeply arched and lateral loops U­shaped and open anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[398,491,599,625]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="36.[264,382,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[300,1317,317,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[264,1323,310,1751]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Diamphidaxona (Diamphidaxonella) brevitarsa sp. nov., adult female. 69, dorsal shield; 70, ventral shield and genital field; 71, pedipalp; 72, gnathosoma, lateral view; 73, leg I; 74, distal segments of leg IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[457,491,599,625]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="70.0">70</number>
</figureCitation>
). Projections covering insertions of fourth pair of legs with anterior extensions moderately long, sinuous and directed anterolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1135,639,665]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="36.[264,382,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[300,1317,317,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[264,1323,310,1751]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Diamphidaxona (Diamphidaxonella) brevitarsa sp. nov., adult female. 69, dorsal shield; 70, ventral shield and genital field; 71, pedipalp; 72, gnathosoma, lateral view; 73, leg I; 74, distal segments of leg IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[1101,1135,639,665]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="70.0">70</number>
</figureCitation>
). Fourth pair of legs with tarsi short and stocky (
<figureCitation box="[680,775,679,705]" captionStart="FIGURES 69 – 74" captionStartId="36.[264,382,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[300,1317,317,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[264,1323,310,1751]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 69 – 74. Diamphidaxona (Diamphidaxonella) brevitarsa sp. nov., adult female. 69, dorsal shield; 70, ventral shield and genital field; 71, pedipalp; 72, gnathosoma, lateral view; 73, leg I; 74, distal segments of leg IV." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[741,775,679,705]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="74.0">74</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
